On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, the date on which the first passengers enter the metro, tram and bus with an electronic voucher in their pockets instead of a paper ticket is written in the history of the Prague Transport Company.
This can now be purchased by almost one hundred thousand people who own the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase the 30-day, 90-day and annual voucher (this will be valid as of January 1, 2009) and simultaneously load it onto their chip card at the transport company’s information centres and stations at the Metro, Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, N<0xC3><0xA1>dra<0xC5><0xBE><0xC3><0xAD> Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Lezty, and Lu<0xC5><0xBE>ty.
The bonuses can be purchased from yesterday on the Internet on the pages of the transport company, www.dpp.cz.
